Based on your address and phone number, the 9-1-1 service associated with your Digital Home Phone Service is: Basic 9-1-1 Service.//
                   //
                   Basic 9-1-1 service is different from Enhanced 9-1-1 service that is available on most traditional telephone services.//
                   //
                   If you dial 9-1-1, you will be automatically routed to a specialized call centre that handles emergency calls. The call centre is different from the Public Safety Answering Point (PSAP) that could answer a traditional emergency call. You will be required to provide your name, telephone number and address to the call centre operator.//
                   //
                   9-1-1 Service will NOT be available if your Internet connection is down or your Digital Home Phone service is not available, e.g. in the case of a power failure. //
                   //
                   9-1-1 Service may not be available when calling from outside of Canada. //
                   //
                   Please refer to Primus’ Terms of Use for full terms and conditions related to 9-1-1 service associated with your Digital Home Phone Service. More information and user tips are available at primus.ca/dhp911. //
                   //
                   1)	I have read and understood the important information regarding 9-1-1 service. What is this? (link this to primus.ca/dhp911)//
                   2)	My 9-1-1 service type as described above is correct and I understand and will inform all users of the Digital Home Phone Service of the nature and limitations of the 9-1-1 service I will receive. //
                   3)	At any time, if I change the address in which I will use my Digital Home Phone Service, I must immediately contact Primus Canada, and that failure to do so may adversely affect my 9-1-1 service. //
